gTile Keyboard Shortcuts
------------------------
Super+Enter - open 

Space  - to change the grid scheme [optional]
Enter  - and the window will resize
Escape - to cancel resize

Configured presets
------------------
Accelerator key binding for preset
Window will resize  - GUI stays open
Alternatively, enable "Auto close on keyboard shortcut" 

Shortcuts
---------
Pre-configured

Super+Alt      - Grid 2x2
Super+Control  - Grid 2x3
Super+Shift    - Grid 3x3

Grid selectors are combined with a keypad number to define placement


Shortcuts for Super+Alt+KP_1-9

KP_1 - Bottom left quarter of screen
KP_2 - Bottom half
KP_3 - Bottom right quarter
KP_4 - Center left
KP_5 - Center
KP_6 - Center right
KP_7 - Top left quarter
KP_8 - Top half
KP_9 - Top right quarter

Shortcuts are optimized for horizontal screens
For **cyclable presets**, invoke the corresponding shortcut consecutively on a window to activate format variants.


Auto Tiling  - All windows on screen
------------------------------------
Open gTile
Click autotile buttons, or
Press one of `[1..9,0]` (total 10 available) for vertical columns autotiling, or
M "main" autotiling

Press `M` multiple times to cycle through variants
Main variables are configurable.

Autogrow - fill available space to neighbors
--------------------------------------------
Default shortcut <Alt><Ctrl>s

Focus window to expand
Open gTile
Press <Alt><Ctrl>s - windows snap to neighbors

Window Spacing and Insets
-------------------------
Optionally configure an inset and spacing

Gnome-shell shortcuts
---------------------
Super+Up - Maximize
Super+Down - Un-Maximize (return to size and position previous to maximizing)
Super+Left/Right - left/right half of screen
Shift+Super+Up/Down/Left/Right - move window to adjacent monitor/workspace
